For those who have not gotten on board yet... Here is a short trailer for our insanely ambitious, beautiful, and timely series DISCONNECTED (Disconnected_Series). Link to series in Profile 

We gathered together a bunch of creatives from around the world (U.S., India, U.K., Rwanda) to produce a series set against the backdrop of the global pandemic and the movement for equality. The stories are loosely connected but the themes are universal. In what MovieMaker has called “a Steven Soderbergh kind of ambition and scope,” all participants are shooting with the best equipment available while adhering to social distancing rules.

This project has been so challenging but also so inspirational to work on. Creatives from all over the world coming together to hold up a mirror to what we are all experiencing in this unbelievable moment in time. Check it out. You won’t be disappointed.

DISCONNECTED
"In the midst of a global pandemic, a group of friends from around the world reconnect while managing the new challenges in front of them."

Created by Matthew Leutwyler & Anton Laines.

Trailer created by Milomix Productions.
Edited and Produced by Chris Miloslavich

I used to dread hitting my protein goals. Now, I actually look forward to it !! 🤤 Thankaaa @manitimehtaoza for this deliciousness !!! 🤍💪🏽

PROTEIN SMOOTHIE 

INGREDIENTS:

1. Vanilla Protein Powder - 1 scoop 
2. First fruit of choice - 100 grams
3. Second Fruit of choice - 100 grams 
4. Greek Yogurt/Low Fat Dahi - 100 grams
5. Milk of choice - 100 ml 
6. Chia Seeds/Psyllium Husk - 10 grams/1 tbs
7. Walnuts - 1 half 

OPTIONAL: You can freeze the fruit overnight or add ice if you want the smoothie extra cold. 

NOTE: I have been using only strawberries since it's strawberry season and I'm obsessed. 

RECIPE:
*serves 1 

1. In a blender, add the protein powder, both fruits, yogurt/dahi, milk, chia seeds/psyllium husk and blend well. 
2. Pour into a glass. 
3. Crush the walnut, on top. 
4. DRINK UP !

From our kitchen to yours: Eton Mess, a messy & delicious Christmas tradition. 🎄🐽🤍

ETON MESS RECIPE 

INGREDIENTS: 

1. Almond Meringue x 5 (We get ours from Gaylord Bakery Churchgate) 
2. Strawberries x 500 gms 
3. Vanilla Ice Cream x 5 scoops 
4. Sugar x 2 tsp

RECIPE:
*serves 5
*you'll need 5 dessert bowls

1. The night before, cut the strawberries into small squares and mix in the sugar. Refrigerate overnight.
2. Right before serving. Roughly crush 1 meringue in each bowl. 
3. Add a few spoons of strawberries on top of the crushed meringues. 
4. Add 1 scoop of ice cream to each bowl. 
5. Serve. 
6. GOBBLE GOBBLE GOBBLE !!
